<p>In PHP when I use the <code>ord</code> function in order to catch the ASCII code of my character I get this behavior:</p>  <pre><code>ord("a") // return 97 chr(97) // return a </code></pre>  <p>But when I use a special character like <code>Œ</code> the returns are different:</p>  <pre><code>ord("Œ") // return 197 chr(197) // return � </code></pre>  <p>All of my pages are encoded in utf8. This behaviour is the same for most of the special characters.</p>  <p>Has somebody seen this problem in the past? How can I fix it?</p>